snippet.textDisplay:
Funny that! They said the exact same thing about Chisora. And Klitschko. And Fury battered the pair of them. Joshua's movement isn't good enough to beat Fury, particularly that of his head. Fury will win by a stoppage or KO in round 5 or 6. Joshua has a suspect chin and Fury hasn't been knocked out or stopped before. After getting up from that right hand and left hook combo in the 12th round I can't see Joshua's right hand over the top or his uppercuts being that much of the problem. The bloke has an iron chin. And that's assuming that Joshua can land them in the first place.


Fury will retire unbeaten I think. He'll beat Wilder (again!) and Joshua and become the unified champion. Then there'll be a rematch clause for the Joshua fight so Fury will have to sign another three fight contract. Then he'll beat Joshua again and defend his titles twice before retiring, probably against Whyte and Usyk if Joshua doesn't fancy getting seven shades beaten out of him for a third time.
